# App Store Scraper – Project standards

**Shared baseline:** This directory also includes **symlinks** to **`mac-ai`** (engineering principles, documentation/changelog habits, AI guidelines, test-vs-code + Stryker, TypeScript standards). Run **`npm run cursor-rules:sync`** after clone if **`mac-ai`** is a sibling under **`mac-project`**. Clones without **`mac-ai`** keep only this file and **`testing.mdc`** until you run sync.

## Stack and layout

- **Stack**: TypeScript (ESM), Node ≥20, Vitest, Zod, tsup. Core logic in **`src/lib/*.ts`**; types in **`src/types/`**.

## Documentation (this package)

- **JSDoc** for public APIs; **README** for user-facing behavior.
- **`CHANGELOG.md`** at **this package root** (not **`mac-prototype`** paths): substantial changes only (skip minuscule churn).

## External data

- Validate API/HTML responses with Zod schemas from **`src/lib/schemas.ts`**. Prefer **`safeParse`** and throw clear errors on failure.

## Security

- Do not interpolate user/options (e.g. `country`, `collection`, `category`, `sort`) into URLs without validating against allowlists (e.g. `markets`, `Collection`, `Category`). See **`docs/CODE-REVIEW.md`**.

## Design and deferred work

- **Design decisions:** **`docs/DEV-DECISIONS.md`** — consult and update for non-obvious choices (API vs scraping, token handling, etc.).
- **Postponed work:** **`docs/POSTPONED.md`** — check before implementing deferred enhancements (new options, store-specific behavior, parity).
